snippet.description:

Houston, a kid with anger management problems is once again being recorded by his brother. It’s hard to tell if this one is fake, but if it is they do a very convincing job. And if the brothers’ aim was to make viral videos, surely they wouldn’t have deleted them all from their channel??
Houston rage quits whilst playing Call of Duty.
He then forces his brother to drive him to the store to return the console.
Unfortunately he doesn’t have a receipt.

This next Fortnite gamer is having a very bad time. Things are not going well, and on top of it, his cousin won’t stop teasing him about it. Until he snaps.
Dylan realises how triggered he is and goes outside to cool off, whilst his cousin films the wreckage in disbelief. Ah. Looks like Dylan hadn’t gone outside to cool off…

This next clip starts with a misunderstanding. It quickly becomes clear that the mother and ‘Andy’ have planned to trigger young William. To what end, is unclear. But he starts to get stressed out, and then offers to ‘give them a movie’. However the movie he had in mind was Scarface.
The mother’s prank has totally backfired, or has it?
Rather than addressing the problem of a crazyily disobedient and violent son, she is more focused on getting William to remove the conveniently old TV from the house. On Christmas. Maybe to make room for the brand new one that santa has brought? Could the whole video have been a set-up?

Wings of Redemption often rage quits by destroying his controller. Like a lot. Even taking down other things too. So much so, in fact, he should really consider playing on a Wii…

We all remember violent Jeff from earlier Rage Quit videos… Well he’s about to do it again… He’s already broken 3 controllers and one playstation!

Some kids just shouldn’t be allowed to play such stressful and intense multiplayer games.
And we leave you now with a win! Imagine that wonderful feeling when you get 1st in Fortnite… Now imagine that surrounded by all of your mates…
